Consider a 30-60-90 right triangle. The length of the hypotenuse is given as $2\sqrt{6}$ centimeters. Find the sum of the lengths, in centimeters, of the two legs of this triangle.A 30-60-90 right triangle has the following properties:- The ratio of the lengths of the sides is $1:\sqrt{3}:2$.- The angle measures are 30°, 60°, and 90°. egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (3,0) -- (3,5.196) -- cycle;\draw (1.5,0) arc (0:60:1.5);\draw (3,1) arc (90:30:1);
ode at (0.75,0.3) {$30^\circ$};
ode at (3.2,2.7) {$60^\circ$};
ode at (1.5,-0.3) {$1$};
ode at (3.5,2.598) {$\sqrt{3}$};
ode at (1.8,2.598) {$2$};\end{tikzpicture}
